  "texts": [
    "DATA ANALYSIS 4.1 Awkward Data SupportAlthough sociological analysis of personality is important, currently most available datasets can not support such a thorough analysis.",
    "First, personality labeling needs huge human power, leading to labeled samples far from sufficient in many existing datasets.",
    "Therefore, many datasets [3,5,10] only contain no more than 1,000 samples, which is far from enough for training effective models.",
    "Second, most existing datasets focus on one single modality such as text alone [5], video alone [10], or multi-channel features [16] at the individual level, but none of them contain social environments and users interaction behaviors.",
    "Therefore these datasets can only support individual detection with naive models but are far from enough to explore sociological analysis of one's behavior, personality, and social environments."
  ],
